column13: Upon arriving at our dental practice, how satisfied were you with our greeting?
column14: How satisfied were you with the amount of time spent in our waiting room?
column15: Please rate your comfort level during your appointment?
column16: How satisfied were you with your dental treatment options?
column17: How would you rate your hygienist?
column18: How would you rate your dentist?
column19: How likely are you to refer your friends and family to our dental office?

column20: Excellent dentist, and a great experience with my cleaning appointment last month as well thanks.
Always feels great to come in and see friends:)
I felt very comfortable and very satisfied with the work that was done yesterday.
I don't really talk to people about health and hygiene usually so it would never be brought up in casual conversation

I have been coming to this dental office for 8 years & yesterday was the first time I felt like a complete stranger. Staff was not very welcoming & acted like they did not know me. I was very disappointed with my visit. The interaction with everyone felt forced & robotic there was no “heart” to any conversations it all felt very superficial. Lately I seem to be moved from the dental hygienist I always go to, when booking next appointments I am told it will be with my preferred hygienist but upon arrival for appointments I am always moved to be seeing another hygienist than requested. I have also noticed lately that my benefits coverage is being ignored & finding that the appointments are going over what I am covered for, forcing me to pay more & more out of pocket each visit. I am greatly considering looking for a new dentist office
Especially, this time my dental treatment was not so happy and thinking about so many things. Thanks for improved situation for all patients.
Mary, the hygenist, made me feel comfortable.
Was the first time with Emily and she was amazing!  Looking forward to seeing her again, even though I was nervous going in!!!  Thank you so much!
The new dentist is a great addition to your team
Totally ignored when I checked in.
Little annoyed at how much work went into one tooth, lots of methods went into fixing it, when it should have only been one, felt like i wasted money on one tooth i dont need
Always a pleasure to see Debbie. Debbie is very professional and thoughtful towards her patients
the only problem is sitting in the waiting room baking in the sun and sweating.
You're not supposed to like going to the dentist but I have to say I really don't mind going to Dr. Barr...
This was so comfortable a visit. Instead of waiting six months for my next appointment, I will return after three months (December 2019).

Question 4 was not relevant to my latest appointment.
Girl at the front is new. I'd suggest she greet people when they come in. She did make eye contact, and give me a nod, but some people might not see this as a greeting.
Best dentist i have been to
Thank you for best dental experience in long time.
It’s always a pleasurable experience when I come to get any dental work done.

I don’t normally complain but overall I felt my cleaning was just okay. To me it felt very rushed and I didn’t think a great job was done. Maybe my teeth didn’t need as much cleaning as I thought, but it felt like the hygienist was rushing through it, not completing the cleaning thoroughly, the cleaning hurt more than normal because she was a bit rough, she wasn’t prepared really, and was just a bit messy. Normal practices I’m use to (such as rinsing out my mouth) she did by spraying water in my mouth which I did no t really enjoy. I had to take my own bid off as well and there didn’t seem to be an understanding as to why I was visiting the office that day. Overall I found it rather disappointing and if I wasn’t covered by insurance I likely would have requested my money back.
Avery friendly office very proffesionel servisces
Over the years I have been to different dental offices but Longworth Dental has met all my expectations 🤗

I am a person who fears the dentist but Debbie and Dr Barr have come to enjoy my visits. They listen and comfort and reassure me at every visit. My health issues are no problem for them. Debbie has become a friend over the years. I have sung Dr Barr praise to all who listen.
I have always had extreme fear of dentists. Having been a patient at Longworth Dental has helped a great deal with my fears.

Debbie is a pleasure. 
She can never retire😊
Came in for mouthguards.  Love the scan instead of the moulds!  Kayla was great!
I’m quite happy about my dental treatment. Happy Halloween!!!
Question 4 does not apply.   I was there for a filling.

It is hard for me to do a survey. I don't really like going to the dentist. I was concerned when the dentist thought he was going to fill a different tooth then I thought we had agree on. As for the cleaning, the hygienist was very friendly. But my gums are very sore. I don't remember them every being this sore before after a cleaning. After only every having had cleaning done for many years it is expensive having all this work done.  The staff is very nice and friendly. The hygienist did remind me that I can use the bills on my taxes.
I had a filling done and I was impressed I didn't need any advil when the freezing came out:)
Absolutely fantastic experience with Mary and Debby for both myself and my kids.  Dentist was terrific. Thank you.
Fantastic office, thoroughly impressed on every front
Already gave a reference on social media
I was not impressed with my dentist. I would like to ensure all future work is done by Dr. Barr. I was under the impression that’s who I was seeing today.
I was hesitant about having a different Dentist working on my problem but he was excellent.
Very friendly comfortable atmosphere.  Debbie is great at explaining things. Always gives new ideas for me to improve my oral health
Debbie always does an amazing job.

This place is awesome the staff so nice Dr Barr is the best even though she wasnt there for my visit this time the other dentist is pretty good too i always feel comfortable coming for any dental procedure
I already know my financial options. No need to explain.
Kingsley was very impressed with all the swag he received!
Staffs and Dentist very kind and respect with each and every patient. From the beginning to Untill we step out from the clinic they treat very nicely .
Appointment went really well. Dentist was very professional and explained everything.
Billing was all messed up. Still waiting for a call on final amount. It seems they may have charged more than my benefits cover

The hygienist was very friendly but extremely rough when cleaning my teeth and I had to wait 15 minutes past my 4pm appointment for the hygienist to socialize with others. While having my teeth cleaned she was way to close to me (she had her body pressed right to my head the whole time). Felt like she was in a rush to be done to go home. As well as leaving me through out my cleaning to talk to another client in another cubicle. Not impressed at all.
This appt was for my 4.5 yr old and she is very scared of the dentist. The hygenist and dentist tried their best and were very sweet with her.

New hygienist for me. She knows her stuff but i didn't come out with a very positive feeling. She chats about many things but acts like she is my friend Ann's knows all about me. A comment about Lakeridge Health want welcome after ous spent 10 days there recently and my daughter works there.
Being very nervous, I was treated very well.
Always a great experience here. You have a great team!
Hudson always looks forward to coming to the dentist here. Thank you for making it a comfortable experience for him!

Dr Barr is great! Best dentist I have ever had! She explains procedures and is a good listener. 
Thank you
As much as I dislike going to the dentist, I find your office to be the best I’ve experienced.

I told the hygienist about cleaning my teeth longer then what’s covered and when I paid it was two and a half units of time and she said not a word about it. I have told the receptionist and now the hygienist about extra charges without knowing and it still happened so let customer know!

I Am said that Debbie dnd Emily left. I hope whomever you
get to replace them is as good and better than them.
I experienced a cheerful, bright and efficient environment.
I had a tooth that I was concerned about that was bothering me and the dds didn’t even examine it.

I always have great hygienists and exams. The only issue was that upon concluding I was advised I owed $63 from emergency xrays and exam last year. I have never had an emergency and my appt are booked based on my coverage which is 100% covered if the alotted time has gone by. Any exams and xrays offered have been met by a response from me of only if covered. Each time they have then checked and said yes. So I am at a loss for how I have funds owed.
It is amazing how the practice has changed over the last year. It is not the same feeling as experienced in the past. It certainly has grown exponentially and has more of a business feel.
The only reason I gave my wait time a 4 was because my appt. Was for 11:30am and I was called to come in for 11 instead but ended up waiting until 11:30.

Love the office first off, it was the hygienist that didn’t work for me. She may work fine on others but my experience was not pleasant. Was rough and didn’t seem to have control in the room by dropping equipment not attaching equipment properly and coming apart. Room not setup properly.
I rated comfort at 7 and that is a great score for me.

For a standard cleaning and check from the dentist, it took over an hour and 15 minutes.  The hygienist couldn't get the xray to work and was rough with inserting the application in the mouth.  The cleaning process was very painful with the new technology being used.  I was sprayed in the face on numerous occasions and the hygienist was rough with the "moisture sucker" - making me gag.  I finally had to ask her to stop and use the manual cleaning tools.  Overall, this was the most painful and uncomfortable experience at the office.

I had the new one named Andrea, she is very sweet and pleasant and very thorough but when she was scraping my teeth with the new water scraper she kept hitting my gums and my teeth are oretty sore today, but having said that my teeth feel so smooth and amazing

I quite enjoyed my visit to Longworth Dental. It was very nice to meet Pria. Pria was very professional and had some helpful information for me.  I would recommend Longworth Dental to everyone I know.
Great appointment! My new crown feels great!!!
We love our dentist’s whole office!!
It was much better this time. I explained what had happened last time and she worked with me. All good! thanks.
I am a very nervous patient and I was made to feel relaxed and everything was explained as we went along. Positive experience indeed.

I have always felt really good about your dental office. During my last two visits I have been encouraged to buy very expensive services (braces) or items (electric toothbrushes). While I appreciate wanting your clients to be aware of good dental health, upon reflection afterward, l feel like there’s now a “sales” aspect to my visits. My previous dental hygienist, Debbie, is no longer there. Debbie NEVER pressured me to buy. She was honest, thorough and very conscientious of my dental health and did a great job. My last two visits have me considering finding another dentist.

I’m not sure what happened but I felt like everything was super rushed. My hygienist  never introduced herself. She didn’t know my name. The actual cleaning did not seem anywhere as thorough as when I had Deb. I truly missed Deb’s customer service and the experience I had that I had with her. She knew how to treat clients. I did not feel like a valued customer at all.
Hygienist Mary and Dentist Barr are great! So friendly and make me feel very comfortable. Overall great experience!
After asking more than once, the pressure was too much during the water pik scaling. Too rough. She wasn't my usual hygenist.
Did not enjoy my experience with the hygenist. She was very negative and talked as if she knew everything. I would not go back to her again.
Amazing service - always happy - very accommodating
Dr. Aryan was the best dental experience I’ve ever had. I had ABSOLUTELY PAINLESS experience. Such a nice, welcoming, polite gentleman. Will come back again for sure.
Already referred my daughter to Longworth Dental, also mentioned it to a few people looking for a good and honest dental practice
I was sad to see my usual hygienist is no longer with the dental office.😢
Great dentist and team thank you
Mary was amazing with my son. He was so worried when we got there and by the end he was laughing! Thanks 😊
great fast treatment of lost filling. Tooth hasn't felt this good in awhile.
Everything went on smooth i felt comfortable and welcomed. Every one is so nice and friendly.

This is my second cleaning where the hygienist kept hitting my upper front teeth and lower teeth when bringing the instruments (mirror, pick, or polisher) into and out of my mouth. I don’t expect to end up with a chipped tooth during a dental cleaning appointment. The hygienist was extremely friendly and personable; however, more attention to detail is required to ensure the comfort of the client.
Having to submit reimbursement claim is a negative.  Although appt was at 9, didn’t get called into room until at least 9:06.  Had another appt at 10 to get to, but hygienist did get me out in time.

Second time I’ve waited over 30 minutes. After showing up just before my appointment. Hygienist didn’t stop talking about herself while I was getting my mouth frozen which was frankly annoying. Dentist left In the middle of my filling and came back after 15 minutes for an unknown reason. No regard for his hand digging into my chin after asking to move it. We will be looking at other dentist offices. Hygienist continually dripped water over my neck continually.
Could my husband have a consultation with doctor Barr?
I had a supply hygenist that was not very good. She did not know how to work the tools and did not provide a very good cleaning.
Prices just keep on going up.

On the whole everyone was very professional, I was early so my wait time was wasn't a problem at all. Something seems to be missing, I think perhaps it used to have a friendlier atmosphere when entering. Might of just been the time of day & workload. Overall I'm happy with everyone.
I really like this dental office, but very disappointed that I have to pay and submit my own claim now.  This is why I wouldn’t recommend you.
I don’t like paying out of pocket when my benefits cover payments

Was just a cleaning so didn't see my dentist. However, the dental hygienist was great,  and I feel horrible for forgetting her name, but I was extremely happy with my visit. So much I took the time to fill out a survey, which I never do.
I am amazed and thankful for patience and talent exhibited with my young children. Thank you.

Changing your charges to the patients directly during a pandemic while income for some is in question is utterly immoral and you should be ashamed. 

Making people choose between dental care and food/rent is in appropriate and we won't be back

Go back to direct billing the insurance companies
Just don’t like worrying about getting reimbursed for payment
Thank you so so much for getting me in quickly!! Dr Barr is amazing and the staff is wonderful.
Do not want the hygienist I had again.

Was not happy that nobody told me that u guys don’t do direct billing anymore before my appointment.  So I had a 450$ bill that I was not expecting. I will be looking for a new dentist that does direct billing moving forward.
Very good and I enjoyed it.
About 15 minutes late. Other than that perfect.
Thank you for everything. Everyone was pleasant.
I appreciate everyone there for taking good care of me and for being so gosh darn friendly. Brings a tear to me eyes!

Dr Ali poorly explained what was wrong with my teeth (I.e. saying I had a “decay” instead of just saying “cavity”). I felt very uncomfortable with the dentist and I am having difficulty trusting his diagnosis/recommendation.

I text to let the office know I was waiting in the car. They called me right in however, I had to wait almost 15 minutes in the waiting area, while it filled up with other patients coming in and going out. I would have preferred to wait in the car until they were ready to take me in.
Thanks for your excellent dental services.
Clear and transparent communication about recommended treatment plans, including visuals are key for me.  Evidence based information helps me make informed decisions and deal with amy anxiety.

Dr Barr and her team are awesome. Dr Barr has excellent bed
Side manners and listens. She is a people person and her
Professional work as a dentist is above average
 She cares about her patients. All my visits have been positive
The hygienist was particularly great - most comfortable cleaning I've ever had
My daughter loved her visit! She said everyone was so helpful and nice.
Very expensive for 4 fillings. Was surprised 45min of work was $800.00.
Will be bringing my entire family here!
Felt very comfortable,dr Barr is awesome and explained everything thoroughly. Highly recommend longworth dental.
Am super happy with my hygienist 🤩

Because I paid for our employees dental plan. I would love to have rates somehow be lowered by ontario dentist. To continue our plan we already had to go to a 9 month checkup rather than a 6 month. Maybe something that can be brought up to the Ontario dental group. I know dentist want the best for all clients.
Overall I was very satisfied about today’s treatment. Thanks.

The dentist was very nice and professional. But during the procedure I was experiencing pain in the location and I did mention this. When home the pain persisted and the next day (today) it is still there. I have never experienced pain after fillings before. When I work up today my jaw cracked once, loudly when I yawned. It has never done that before. I took a Tylenol last night and another this morning. I have never had to take pain meds after fillings. My mouth was not sure at all before the fillings - I did not know there were any cavities until this was mentioned after the X-rays - I’m surprised there were 4 when I come every 6 months for a cleaning.
Thank you so much. Love DR BARR. Always gets me in when I have an emergency. Very Caring and makes me feel at ease. Staff is very friendly and caring. Thank you all so much. ❤️
Pleased with covid precautions. My hygienist was thorough & thoughtful of my comfort. The dentist gave clear explanations of my xrays. I wouldn't hesitate to recommend to friends.
Thank you Dr. Barr! You are a master at your craft!
Recognizing that waiting rooms need to be reduced due to COVID, the waiting area is not very comfortable while having to wait.
I love Cassidy! Give Cassidy a raise!!!

I have no concerns regarding Dr.Barr and staff. I am not satisfied with the billing, The charges always seem to come out higher than what was guoted and the fact that you charge up front and then submit the invoice to the insurance company. That was not something that was done when we first started with Longworth Dental

Please ignore previous survey I submitted. Be sure to tell all involved that I didn’t read the instructions the first time. 
Peter

Dr Barr is an exceptional person. She listens
 And helps to problem solve what the concerns 
Are.  Provides solutions and never gives up on her
Clients. Dr Barr also has a team of professionals
And receptionists that provide excellent customer 
Service which reflects her standards for her 
Practice. To know her is to respect her
Thanks everybody
Everyone is awesome :). Thanks so much!

I can say I truly enjoy going to the dentist. I have no fear of how the out come may be. 
I thank you all for your service.
Only disappointing thing is that you are no longer doing direct billing and I have to pay upfront first.
Will be switching offices due to the billing situation now as will numerous family members unfortunately
Great service, friendly staff, clean and respectful environment. And to top it off, my teeth feel great!
I commented to Cassidy what a good job she did and didnt hurt me ay all. She is very nice and made me feel comfortable. Would like to have her everytime for my cleanings.
Dr Barr is fantastic, her attention to patient comfort makes going to the dentist tolerable, haha.

WONDERFUL AS WELL AS A DENTAL APPOINTMENT CAN BE.
DR. BARR VERY KNOWLEDGABLE, CONSIDERATE AND  MADE ME FEEL COMFORTABLE.
FRONT DESK STAFF SECOND TO NONE

I do not like the fact that you have changed the billing and I need to pay up front now very unacceptable in today’s society when I pay for good benefits and there has never been an issue in the past. Emily and Melissa are gone from the front desk and now the feeling of being family is gone when I walk in there. I unfortunately have started to look for a new office to fulfill my family’s dental needs.

I couldn't understand why I was tasting blood an hour after my scaling.  Turns out I had 2 small cuts on my upper front gum line.  I would only refer people if they know ahead of time they have to pay for their services and wait for reimbursement from their benefits.  Some people do not have the means to afford that.
Very patient with my son who was very nervous and wouldn't let the hygienist do very much. Hoping for a better outcome next time we come. Thank you for a great first experience there!
I know it’s hard to talk with your mouth open but a little more small talk would be welcomed.
Thank you for your great service!
I got the best possible treatment!
Service all good. Have to work with what you have!

Everything went very well, I will be back.....but hopefully not to soon.

Bruce

Dr Barr’s team reflects her high expectations 
For excellent client service. The environment 
Is positive and professional. Everyone
Is greeted with a smile and you feel welcomed
From the moment you step in the door.
Dr Barr is always mindful of your feelings and 
Provides options for your personal dental work
 Before she proceeds. 
Dr Barr is a doctor but she is very kind and 
Personable. I’m 62years of age and I’ve had
Many dentist’s in my life  but Dr Barr has got 
What it takes to be very successful in her career.
She is a people person. 
Thanks everyone for taking good care of me
Helena
Dr. Barr is just the sweetest, nicest person and the best dentist I have ever had. She is kind and caring and put me at ease in what would otherwise be an unpleasant experience.
Please provide an estimate before procedures begin. Otherwise an excellent experience.

I have just finished having a root canal and crown done. I was very pleased with the work and the speed that I was given my appts. but was disappointed aesthetically with the look of the tooth because I ended  up with an onlay rather than a crown and my tooth is 2 different colours. With it being a bicuspid it shows when I smile.There was no difference in price so it would have been nice to have the whole tooth covered.
My hygienist was the best I've ever had. Explained everything so well, was so helpful!
Great as always, regardless of who I have poking my teeth
From the smiling faces at reception to hygienist, Bella to Dr. Ismail, I thank you! Your professionalism shines through those smiling eyes! Thank you all so much! Patricia
Happy I joined this dental office I liked the dentist and the staff

I was a little shocked at the price of the extraction. I had thought it would be less than $200. I didn't get a receipt cuz the computers weren't working properly, but I think it was probably from the additional xray. I just didn't expect to cost that much. Everyone was really amazing and kind though! Hoping to transfer our family of 6 over!
You're all fantastic, you've helped me out so much and I appreciate it! :)

Thank you for getting me in. It’s nice to know that I can count on coming in every 3 months, and that I’m not getting pushed out of the schedule. As a family member, I know that our regular clients come first. At the same time, my oral health is important to me, and I’m happy to be back on a regular schedule. Thank you to the admin team for getting me in, and to the hygiene team for taking care of me.

I didn't enjoy this visit and may not return.  I got many reminders for the appointment saying you need 2 days notice to move or cancel, but that doesn't apply to the office i guess.  When i arrived there was no hygienist.  I am okay with things coming up, but i should have been called and offered to move the entire appointment.  My time is valuable as well, and coming twice for what should have been a single visit was not right. I also didn't know how to process the dentist telling me about how a if this cavity isn't filled soon it will progress into my bones on the first visit and it felt very awkward.  Didn't say oh, maybe we should check this again on your next visit to see if it has progressed, went straight to suggesting work be done.  I went to previous dentist office for 30 years, and they didn't feel i needed a filling in all that time.  During the 30 years i saw 3 different dentists there and as recently as 4 months ago.  First visit here and i need 2 fillings right away.  I am sure the dentist is great and very qualified, but i didn't get along with their style.
your whole clinic is the best...thanks for looking after me
Very happy with Longworth Dental last couple of visits,  both Oct 5 &  Sept 28. No concerns. Thank you.
Thank you Dr Barr and her team.
You do not direct bill anymore and the staff changeover is constant
The water tasted horrible from the mouth-sprayer when suction was used.  Hopefully it could be treated in near future.

We still struggle when we see the constant staff turn over.  I haven’t had the same hygienist in the last two years…makes one wonder what the problem is?!  Isabelle was great, gentle and met my needs-so that’s not the issue.  I didn’t know that my polishing and dentist assessment wouldn’t be covered by my insurance…I would have forgone these had I known…
For number 3 after the gas a 10 lol
In terms of referral to family/friends, I generally don't do this. However, if asked, I would tell them that we have had very positive experience with Longworth Dental.
I have a fear of dentist. But still come every 4 months because I know I am treated with respect. & compassion.
I’ve always felt comfortable and at ease at Longworth Dental. I have recommended Longworth Dental to my daughter.
Teeth were polished for the first time in many visits. This was very important to me.

I was absolutely TERRIFIED for my first ever filling and everyone was incredible. They went out of their way to comfort, make sure I was aware of everything going on, and ensured I was calmer before starting. Thank you all so much!
No comment at this time, Have a Happy Holidays and Merry Christmas all!
I'm a very nervous patient but Cassidy put me at ease and I had one of my best experiences with way she conducted my cleaning. Booked my next cleaning with her.  Thanks
As it was a root canal, I wasn’t widely anticipating it ! However everything was well explained, professional and lowered my uncertainty.
Every patient is  treated like you are special

I was booked for cleaning.  Asked about repairing a chip.  Filling fell out during cleaning.  Was able to have new filling put in.
Because I had not prepared myself for the filling I was quite stressed by the idea of the filling, the procedure.
I had not budgeted for the extra cost and was very shaky during and after procedure.
Overall the work was unavoidable, well done but I was a wreck
Bella is absolutely amazing, she is so gentle. Would highly recommend :)
In and out quick and painless
I love coming to the dentist because of you!
First time with both the hygienist, and the dentist… As per the usual, both exceeded expectations. Thank you
My son loves going to the dentist.  Everyone is always very friendly. Thank you to the ladies at the front desk.  They were great with my son also.
Thank you very much to the Dentist and Dental Hygienists that worked with me.  I’m very pleased with the service and results.
Prefer direct billing. Wish you would change get back.
The hygienist that I had on three seperate occasions used the saliva ejector under my tongye which then was pulled when it caught my sublingual papilla. This has since caused swelling and discomfort.
I would only refer family and friends if they can afford to pay for services when full coverage is available.  This is the only office in Bowmanville with this demand.
I applaud the hygenist  she was patiend and made jason feel comfortable👏👏👏
Excellent work by everyone. Thx Doug
I let Bella know that was the most gentle cleaning I had ever had.  Thank you
Not really too keen on the new cleaning method

I came in for an Initial exam, which included an excessive amount of x-rays. And when I asked to have my lingual wire reglued, the dentist did so, but did not tell me ahead of time that he was going to charge me 4 times as much as what my previous dentists have charged. And then when I asked why it cost so much the front desk just told me, normally we tell you ahead of time what the cost is, but I guess we didn't do that. And on top of that I was told that this was a standard code for this procedure which I know isn't true because of my previous experience with this same procedure. So obviously this clinic just cared about getting the most amount of money possible out of their patients by charging procedures as the most expensive code they can find. You guys obviously thought to over charge, since you knew I have insurance. But I have very limited dental coverage and now I will have to wait until the new year before I can even get a cleaning. I will definitely not be coming back and would recommend anyone I know to avoid this clinic.
Thank you Dr.Barr.  you are fantastic
Amazing work done by Dr Barr. Four cavities and no freezing. That made my day. Thank you so much
It was great returning back to Longworth Dental and seeing Dr. Barr and her staff. I always value/trust her opinion for dental work
please make up your mind b4 charging Ramsey $200 for 3 visits then sending ramsey a text message to go and see a specilist
Thank you for having a hygienist that has explained things and helped to lowere anxiety . I am looking forward to future visits with Bella
Was disappointed that there were no supplies - dental picks and floss for bridge - available at my visit
The only negative experience was with the exrays...I wish there was a less painful procedure - perhaps using child size in the future

This is by far the friendliest team I've ever met!
I always feel super comfortable and welcomed in this facility.
Keep up the amazing job!

This is by far the friendliest team I've ever met!
I always feel super comfortable and welcomed in this facility.
Keep up the amazing job!
Love the people who work in the office. Cost for services appear not to be consistent . I have insurance but that is no reason not to not question the cost for services
Love the people who work in the office. Cost for services appear not to be consistent . I have insurance but that is no reason not to not question the cost for services

Both dentist and hygienist were super understanding and helpful during the needle portion of my appointment. I have a fear of needles and I felt so supported through it, they took their time and talked me through it. I appreciate it so much.

Both dentist and hygienist were super understanding and helpful during the needle portion of my appointment. I have a fear of needles and I felt so supported through it, they took their time and talked me through it. I appreciate it so much.
Good experience but the kids and I both commented on how rough our hygienists were. We havenât had this issue before ;)

Just an amazing staff at this Dentist Office highly reccomended to all.
Just an amazing staff at this Dentist Office highly reccomended to all.
Thanks for keeping my teeth healthy and explaining the procedures I had before beginning the treatment.
Thanks for keeping my teeth healthy and explaining the procedures I had before beginning the treatment.
Our dental hygienist was Cassidy.    She did an excellent job - professional, efficient and empathetic to our needs.
Our dental hygienist was Cassidy.    She did an excellent job - professional, efficient and empathetic to our needs.
Best cleaning I’ve probably ever had…thanks!
Best cleaning I’ve probably ever had…thanks!
Everyone is always very pleasant and welcoming.
Everyone is always very pleasant and welcoming.
Everyone at this dental office has made all of my experiences as comfortable as possible to date. Thank you all!
Everyone at this dental office has made all of my experiences as comfortable as possible to date. Thank you all!
Staff and environment could not have been more welcoming , friendly and personable
Staff and environment could not have been more welcoming , friendly and personable
We don’t have family here and all our friends are old and have their own dentists. If we did however talk to someone looking for a dentist we would mention Longworth Dental.
We don’t have family here and all our friends are old and have their own dentists. If we did however talk to someone looking for a dentist we would mention Longworth Dental.
Great job, happy canada day to all
Great job, happy canada day to all
You guys make going to the dentist actually fun a very attentive and knowledgeable staff, i look forward to my next visit , !!!
